Assign these roles to individual users already in the system or to user groups: 
  
  • CMP Root Administrator (sn_cmp.cmp_root_admin): Provides unrestricted access to all Cloud Provisioning and Governance functions. 
  • Cloud Administrator (sn_cmp.cloud_admin): Access to all Cloud Provisioning and Governance functions, but can only make changes to the accounts and resources the user owns.
  • Cloud Group Admin (sn_cmp.cloud_group_admin): Access to all Cloud Provisioning and Governance functions for accounts and resources belonging to all of the groups to which this user belongs.
  • Cloud Governor (sn_cmp.cloud_governor): Monitors overall cloud usage and enforces compliance of the organization's rules, quotas, and policies. Also manages tags and permissions to various objects. 
  • Cloud Service Designer (sn.cmp.cloud_service_designer): Authorizes access to the blueprint designer which allows creation of blueprints, importing ARM and CloudFormation templates, and publishing catalog items.
  • Cloud User (sn_cmp.cloud_service_user): Requests and manages stacks and resources through the Cloud User Portal.
  • Cloud Operator (sn_cmp.cloud_operator): Monitors and troubleshoots the Cloud Provisioning and Governance application. 
  • Cloud event integration (sn_cmp.cloud_event_integration): Authorizes access to the instance for external cloud event integration, such as with Azure Monitor Activity Log Alerts. This role gives the access to the cloud event REST endpoint.

Refer to the following links to assign roles for individual cloud service provider users required to access Cloud Provisioning and Governance modules:

  • Assign roles to AWS users of Cloud Provisioning and Governance
  • Assign roles to Azure users of Cloud Provisioning and Governance
  • Assign roles to VMware users of Cloud Provisioning and Governance
  • Assign roles to Google Cloud Platform users of Cloud Provisioning and Governance
  • Assign roles to IBM Cloud users of Cloud Provisioning and Governance
